This article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate. The letter discusses the continuation of a national emergency with respect to weapons of mass destruction. The National Emergencies Act states that a national emergency will automatically terminate unless the President publishes a notice in the Federal Register and transmits it to Congress before the anniversary date of its declaration. In accordance with this provision, Obama states that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 12938, pertaining to the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, will continue for one year beyond November 14, 2010.